        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 3:41PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 341 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 19 miles southeast of Thatcher to over
Starkville, or extending from 41 miles east of Trinidad to over
Trinidad, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southeastern Las Animas County.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
